metadata:
  section_id: 24
  section_name: Chapter 24
  hadith_first: 138
  hadith_last: 145

hadiths[8]{hadithnumber,text,grades,reference,international_number,narrator_chain,chapter_intro}:
138,"""The family of Muhammad (Allah bless him and give him peace) did not satisfy their appetite with barley-bread for before even two consecutive days until Allah’s Messenger (Allah bless him and give him peace) was taken from this world.”",,,48853,"'A’isha said:",Chapter 24
139,"""There was never more than a bare sufficiency of barley- bread for the people of the household of Allah’s Messenger (Allah bless him and give him peace).”",,,48854,"Abu Umama al-Bahili say:",Chapter 24
140,"""Allah’s Messenger (Allah bless him and give him peace) used to spend night after night starving. He and his family would not have any supper to eat, and most of their bread was barley-bread.”",,,48855,"Ibn 'Abbas said:",Chapter 24
141,"“Did Allah’s Messenger (Allah bless him and give him peace) eat the finest flour, meaning white bread?” Sahl said: “Allah’s Messenger (Allah bless him and give him peace) did not see the finest flour until he met Allah (Almighty and Glorious is He).” Then he was asked: “Did you have sieves in the time of Allah’s Messenger (Allah bless him and give him peace)?” He said: “We did not have sieves.” He was asked: “How did you treat barley?” He said: “We used to blow on it, so whatever flew would fly off it, and then we would knead it.”",,,48856,"Sahl ibn Sa'd said that he was asked:",Chapter 24
142,"“Allah’s Prophet (Allah bless him and give him peace) did not eat food on a table, nor in a bowl, and no bread rolled thin and flat was baked for him. I asked Qatada: ‘So on\nwhat were they used to eating?’ He said: ‘On these pieces of skin .”",,,48857,"Anas ibn Malik said:",Chapter 24
143,"""I went in to see 'A'isha, so she ordered a meal for me, and she said: “I do not eat my fill from a meal, for I feel like weeping, if I have not wept.” I said: “Why?” She said:\n“I remember the state in which Allah’s Messenger (Allah bless him and give him peace) departed from this world. By Allah, he did not eat his fill of bread and meat twice in one day!”",,,48858,"Masruq said:",Chapter 24
144,"""Allah’s Messenger (Allah bless him and give him peace) did not eat his fill of barley-bread for two days in a row until he died.”",,,48859,"'A’isha said:",Chapter 24
145,"“Allah’s Messenger (Allah bless him and give him peace) did not eat food on a table, and he did not eat bread rolled thin and flat, until he died.”",,,48860,"Anas said:",Chapter 24
